author: BBC Sport
description: Feyenoord skipper Dirk Kuyt announces his retirement, two days after his hat-trick sealed the Dutch club's first title since 1999.
title: Dirk Kuyt: Former Liverpool and Netherlands forward retires after Feyenoord title win

author: talkSPORT
description: Dirk Kuyt has announced his retirement from football just days after his title heroics with Feyenoord. The Dutchman's hat-trick against on the final day against Heracles helped secure his side the Eredivise title - their first since 1999.  The 36-year-old made 39 appearances, scoring 15 goals and assisting seven and he has decided to hang up his boots on a high. Kuyt played a number of positions over his career, starting as a forward and playing in midfield and right-back.
title: Dirk Kuyt: Liverpool hero announces retirement days after hat-trick helps Feyenoord secure Eredivisie title

description: Der frühere niederländische Fußball-Nationalstürmer Dirk Kuyt beendet seine Spielerkarriere, teilte sein Verein Feyenoord Rotterdam mit.
title: Fußball: Niederländer Kuyt beendet Profi-Karriere

author: FourFourTwo
description: Dirk Kuyt has retired to take up a non-playing role at Feyenoord, just three days after his hat-trick secured the Eredivisie title.
title: Kuyt retires after leading Feyenoord to Eredivisie glory
